<font color="#FF0000">BABY KILLERS OR NOT</font><br>
<tt>Sat May 27  0:26:35 US/Eastern 2000
</tt><p>
I found that to talk about Nam, was a no-no for a lots of guys who went to Nam. Why not because they were ashamed of what they had done,but because they figured that no one would believe them, also that they might be classified as Baby Killers or worst. I for one do not talk to much about VietNam because most people still doesn't want to accept that VietNam is something that most of us had to do..Not because we wanted to.I acknowledge that I may have killed women, and kids, but it was not through and act of wilingness but an act of self preservation. In Nam it was very hard to distinguish between the enemy and friendlys.<br>
As many others I have heard the stories of the enemy being thrown out of chopers, but did not witness any such incident in my 2 1/2 yrs over there.<br>
I did expierence an incident where a young child came in among a bunch of men pulled the pin on a grenade and dropped it on the ground killng himself,and three of the men.For those that classify us as a bunch of Baby Killer, I can only say Judge Not lest you Be Judged<br>
Anyone that wants to discuss this with me feel free to e-mail me.As I am not ashamed of anything that I did over there.RLTW
<p><code>-- rayjoy@ipa.net  (Ray J Sonnier) </code><p>


